{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1000,"text":"David Gallo: This is Bill Lange. I'm Dave Gallo."},{"time":4000,"text":"And we're going to tell you some stories from the sea here in video."},{"time":7000,"text":"We've got some of the most incredible video of Titanic that's ever been seen,"},{"time":12000,"text":"and we're not going to show you any of it."},{"time":15000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"The truth of the matter is that the Titanic --"},{"time":20000,"text":"even though it's breaking all sorts of box office records --"},{"time":22000,"text":"it's not the most exciting story from the sea."},{"time":26000,"text":"And the problem, I think, is that we take the ocean for granted."},{"time":29000,"text":"When you think about it, the oceans are 75 percent of the planet."},{"time":31000,"text":"Most of the planet is ocean water."},{"time":33000,"text":"The average depth is about two miles."},{"time":35000,"text":"Part of the problem, I think, is we stand at the beach,"},{"time":37000,"text":"or we see images like this of the ocean,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and you look out at this great big blue expanse, and it's shimmering"},{"time":44000,"text":"and it's moving and there's waves and there's surf and there's tides,"},{"time":47000,"text":"but you have no idea for what lies in there."},{"time":49000,"text":"And in the oceans, there are the longest mountain ranges on the planet."},{"time":51000,"text":"Most of the animals are in the oceans."},{"time":53000,"text":"Most of the earthquakes and volcanoes are in the sea,"},{"time":55000,"text":"at the bottom of the sea."},{"time":57000,"text":"The biodiversity and the biodensity in the ocean is higher, in places,"},{"time":60000,"text":"than it is in the rainforests."},{"time":62000,"text":"It's mostly unexplored, and yet there are beautiful sights like this"},{"time":64000,"text":"that captivate us and make us become familiar with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"But when you're standing at the beach, I want you to think"},{"time":69000,"text":"that you're standing at the edge of a very unfamiliar world."},{"time":71000,"text":"We have to have a very special technology"},{"time":73000,"text":"to get into that unfamiliar world."},{"time":75000,"text":"We use the submarine Alvin and we use cameras,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and the cameras are something that Bill Lange has developed with the help of Sony."},{"time":82000,"text":"Marcel Proust said, \"The true voyage of discovery"},{"time":84000,"text":"is not so much in seeking new landscapes as in having new eyes.\""},{"time":89000,"text":"People that have partnered with us have given us new eyes,"},{"time":91000,"text":"not only on what exists --"},{"time":93000,"text":"the new landscapes at the bottom of the sea --"},{"time":95000,"text":"but also how we think about life on the planet itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"Here's a jelly."},{"time":99000,"text":"It's one of my favorites, because it's got all sorts of working parts."},{"time":101000,"text":"This turns out to be the longest creature in the oceans."},{"time":103000,"text":"It gets up to about 150 feet long."},{"time":106000,"text":"But see all those different working things?"},{"time":108000,"text":"I love that kind of stuff."},{"time":110000,"text":"It's got these fishing lures on the bottom. They're going up and down."},{"time":112000,"text":"It's got tentacles dangling, swirling around like that."},{"time":113000,"text":"It's a colonial animal."},{"time":115000,"text":"These are all individual animals"},{"time":117000,"text":"banding together to make this one creature."},{"time":119000,"text":"And it's got these jet thrusters up in front"},{"time":121000,"text":"that it'll use in a moment, and a little light."},{"time":125000,"text":"If you take all the big fish and schooling fish and all that,"},{"time":128000,"text":"put them on one side of the scale, put all the jelly-type of animals"},{"time":130000,"text":"on the other side, those guys win hands down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"Most of the biomass in the ocean is made out of creatures like this."},{"time":136000,"text":"Here's the X-wing death jelly."},{"time":138000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":142000,"text":"The bioluminescence -- they use the lights for attracting mates"},{"time":145000,"text":"and attracting prey and communicating."},{"time":147000,"text":"We couldn't begin to show you our archival stuff from the jellies."},{"time":151000,"text":"They come in all different sizes and shapes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"Bill Lange: We tend to forget about the fact that the ocean is miles deep"},{"time":157000,"text":"on average, and that we're real familiar with the animals"},{"time":160000,"text":"that are in the first 200 or 300 feet, but we're not familiar"},{"time":164000,"text":"with what exists from there all the way down to the bottom."},{"time":167000,"text":"And these are the types of animals"},{"time":169000,"text":"that live in that three-dimensional space,"},{"time":171000,"text":"that micro-gravity environment that we really haven't explored."},{"time":174000,"text":"You hear about giant squid and things like that,"},{"time":177000,"text":"but some of these animals get up to be approximately 140, 160 feet long."},{"time":181000,"text":"They're very little understood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"DG: This is one of them, another one of our favorites, because it's a little octopod."},{"time":186000,"text":"You can actually see through his head."},{"time":188000,"text":"And here he is, flapping with his ears and very gracefully going up."},{"time":190000,"text":"We see those at all depths and even at the greatest depths."},{"time":193000,"text":"They go from a couple of inches to a couple of feet."},{"time":195000,"text":"They come right up to the submarine --"},{"time":197000,"text":"they'll put their eyes right up to the window and peek inside the sub."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"This is really a world within a world,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and we're going to show you two."},{"time":203000,"text":"In this case, we're passing down through the mid-ocean and we see creatures like this."},{"time":206000,"text":"This is kind of like an undersea rooster."},{"time":208000,"text":"This guy, that looks incredibly formal, in a way."},{"time":211000,"text":"And then one of my favorites. What a face!"},{"time":215000,"text":"This is basically scientific data that you're looking at."},{"time":218000,"text":"It's footage that we've collected for scientific purposes."},{"time":220000,"text":"And that's one of the things that Bill's been doing,"},{"time":222000,"text":"is providing scientists with this first view of animals like this,"},{"time":224000,"text":"in the world where they belong."},{"time":226000,"text":"They don't catch them in a net."},{"time":228000,"text":"They're actually looking at them down in that world."},{"time":230000,"text":"We're going to take a joystick,"},{"time":232000,"text":"sit in front of our computer, on the Earth,"},{"time":234000,"text":"and press the joystick forward, and fly around the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"We're going to look at the mid-ocean ridge,"},{"time":238000,"text":"a 40,000-mile long mountain range."},{"time":240000,"text":"The average depth at the top of it is about a mile and a half."},{"time":242000,"text":"And we're over the Atlantic -- that's the ridge right there --"},{"time":244000,"text":"but we're going to go across the Caribbean, Central America,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and end up against the Pacific, nine degrees north."},{"time":250000,"text":"We make maps of these mountain ranges with sound, with sonar,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and this is one of those mountain ranges."},{"time":255000,"text":"We're coming around a cliff here on the right."},{"time":257000,"text":"The height of these mountains on either side of this valley"},{"time":259000,"text":"is greater than the Alps in most cases."},{"time":261000,"text":"And there's tens of thousands of those mountains out there that haven't been mapped yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264000,"text":"This is a volcanic ridge."},{"time":266000,"text":"We're getting down further and further in scale."},{"time":268000,"text":"And eventually, we can come up with something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"This is an icon of our robot, Jason, it's called."},{"time":273000,"text":"And you can sit in a room like this,"},{"time":275000,"text":"with a joystick and a headset, and drive a robot like that"},{"time":278000,"text":"around the bottom of the ocean in real time."},{"time":280000,"text":"One of the things we're trying to do at Woods Hole with our partners"},{"time":283000,"text":"is to bring this virtual world --"},{"time":285000,"text":"this world, this unexplored region -- back to the laboratory."},{"time":288000,"text":"Because we see it in bits and pieces right now."},{"time":290000,"text":"We see it either as sound, or we see it as video,"},{"time":293000,"text":"or we see it as photographs, or we see it as chemical sensors,"},{"time":295000,"text":"but we never have yet put it all together into one interesting picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"Here's where Bill's cameras really do shine."},{"time":301000,"text":"This is what's called a hydrothermal vent."},{"time":303000,"text":"And what you're seeing here is a cloud of densely packed,"},{"time":306000,"text":"hydrogen-sulfide-rich water"},{"time":308000,"text":"coming out of a volcanic axis on the sea floor."},{"time":312000,"text":"Gets up to 600, 700 degrees F, somewhere in that range."},{"time":315000,"text":"So that's all water under the sea --"},{"time":317000,"text":"a mile and a half, two miles, three miles down."},{"time":319000,"text":"And we knew it was volcanic back in the '60s, '70s."},{"time":322000,"text":"And then we had some hint that these things existed"},{"time":325000,"text":"all along the axis of it, because if you've got volcanism,"},{"time":327000,"text":"water's going to get down from the sea into cracks in the sea floor,"},{"time":331000,"text":"come in contact with magma, and come shooting out hot."},{"time":334000,"text":"We weren't really aware that it would be so rich with sulfides, hydrogen sulfides."},{"time":339000,"text":"We didn't have any idea about these things, which we call chimneys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"This is one of these hydrothermal vents."},{"time":344000,"text":"Six hundred degree F water coming out of the Earth."},{"time":347000,"text":"On either side of us are mountain ranges that are higher than the Alps,"},{"time":351000,"text":"so the setting here is very dramatic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"BL: The white material is a type of bacteria"},{"time":355000,"text":"that thrives at 180 degrees C."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"DG: I think that's one of the greatest stories right now"},{"time":360000,"text":"that we're seeing from the bottom of the sea,"},{"time":362000,"text":"is that the first thing we see coming out of the sea floor"},{"time":364000,"text":"after a volcanic eruption is bacteria."},{"time":366000,"text":"And we started to wonder for a long time,"},{"time":368000,"text":"how did it all get down there?"},{"time":370000,"text":"What we find out now is that it's probably coming from inside the Earth."},{"time":373000,"text":"Not only is it coming out of the Earth --"},{"time":375000,"text":"so, biogenesis made from volcanic activity --"},{"time":377000,"text":"but that bacteria supports these colonies of life."},{"time":380000,"text":"The pressure here is 4,000 pounds per square inch."},{"time":384000,"text":"A mile and a half from the surface to two miles to three miles --"},{"time":386000,"text":"no sun has ever gotten down here."},{"time":389000,"text":"All the energy to support these life forms"},{"time":391000,"text":"is coming from inside the Earth -- so, chemosynthesis."},{"time":394000,"text":"And you can see how dense the population is."},{"time":396000,"text":"These are called tube worms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"BL: These worms have no digestive system. They have no mouth."},{"time":401000,"text":"But they have two types of gill structures."},{"time":403000,"text":"One for extracting oxygen out of the deep-sea water,"},{"time":406000,"text":"another one which houses this chemosynthetic bacteria,"},{"time":410000,"text":"which takes the hydrothermal fluid --"},{"time":413000,"text":"that hot water that you saw coming out of the bottom --"},{"time":416000,"text":"and converts that into simple sugars that the tube worm can digest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421000,"text":"DG: You can see, here's a crab that lives down there."},{"time":423000,"text":"He's managed to grab a tip of these worms."},{"time":425000,"text":"Now, they normally retract as soon as a crab touches them."},{"time":427000,"text":"Oh! Good going."},{"time":429000,"text":"So, as soon as a crab touches them,"},{"time":431000,"text":"they retract down into their shells, just like your fingernails."},{"time":433000,"text":"There's a whole story being played out here"},{"time":435000,"text":"that we're just now beginning to have some idea of"},{"time":437000,"text":"because of this new camera technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439000,"text":"BL: These worms live in a real temperature extreme."},{"time":442000,"text":"Their foot is at about 200 degrees C"},{"time":446000,"text":"and their head is out at three degrees C,"},{"time":449000,"text":"so it's like having your hand in boiling water and your foot in freezing water."},{"time":453000,"text":"That's how they like to live."},{"time":455000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"DG: This is a female of this kind of worm."},{"time":459000,"text":"And here's a male."},{"time":461000,"text":"You watch. It doesn't take long before two guys here --"},{"time":464000,"text":"this one and one that will show up over here -- start to fight."},{"time":467000,"text":"Everything you see is played out in the pitch black of the deep sea."},{"time":470000,"text":"There are never any lights there, except the lights that we bring."},{"time":473000,"text":"Here they go."},{"time":475000,"text":"On one of the last dive series,"},{"time":477000,"text":"we counted 200 species in these areas --"},{"time":479000,"text":"198 were new, new species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"BL: One of the big problems is that for the biologists"},{"time":484000,"text":"working at these sites, it's rather difficult to collect these animals."},{"time":487000,"text":"And they disintegrate on the way up,"},{"time":489000,"text":"so the imagery is critical for the science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"DG: Two octopods at about two miles depth."},{"time":494000,"text":"This pressure thing really amazes me --"},{"time":496000,"text":"that these animals can exist there at a depth"},{"time":499000,"text":"with pressure enough to crush the Titanic like an empty Pepsi can."},{"time":502000,"text":"What we saw up till now was from the Pacific."},{"time":504000,"text":"This is from the Atlantic. Even greater depth."},{"time":506000,"text":"You can see this shrimp is harassing this poor little guy here,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and he'll bat it away with his claw. Whack!"},{"time":511000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"And the same thing's going on over here."},{"time":514000,"text":"What they're getting at is that -- on the back of this crab --"},{"time":517000,"text":"the foodstuff here is this very strange bacteria"},{"time":519000,"text":"that lives on the backs of all these animals."},{"time":521000,"text":"And what these shrimp are trying to do"},{"time":523000,"text":"is actually harvest the bacteria from the backs of these animals."},{"time":526000,"text":"And the crabs don't like it at all."},{"time":528000,"text":"These long filaments that you see on the back of the crab"},{"time":530000,"text":"are actually created by the product of that bacteria."},{"time":534000,"text":"So, the bacteria grows hair on the crab."},{"time":536000,"text":"On the back, you see this again."},{"time":538000,"text":"The red dot is the laser light of the submarine Alvin"},{"time":540000,"text":"to give us an idea about how far away we are from the vents."},{"time":543000,"text":"Those are all shrimp."},{"time":545000,"text":"You see the hot water over here, here and here, coming out."},{"time":547000,"text":"They're clinging to a rock face"},{"time":550000,"text":"and actually scraping bacteria off that rock face."},{"time":553000,"text":"Here's a tiny, little vent that's come out of the side of that pillar."},{"time":558000,"text":"Those pillars get up to several stories."},{"time":560000,"text":"So here, you've got this valley with this incredible alien landscape"},{"time":563000,"text":"of pillars and hot springs and volcanic eruptions and earthquakes,"},{"time":567000,"text":"inhabited by these very strange animals"},{"time":569000,"text":"that live only on chemical energy coming out of the ground."},{"time":571000,"text":"They don't need the sun at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"BL: You see this white V-shaped mark on the back of the shrimp?"},{"time":576000,"text":"It's actually a light-sensing organ."},{"time":578000,"text":"It's how they find the hydrothermal vents."},{"time":580000,"text":"The vents are emitting a black body radiation -- an IR signature --"},{"time":584000,"text":"and so they're able to find these vents at considerable distances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"DG: All this stuff is happening along that 40,000-mile long mountain range"},{"time":591000,"text":"that we're calling the ribbon of life, because just even today,"},{"time":594000,"text":"as we speak, there's life being generated there from volcanic activity."},{"time":598000,"text":"This is the first time we've ever tried this any place."},{"time":600000,"text":"We're going to try to show you high definition from the Pacific."},{"time":603000,"text":"We're moving up one of these pillars."},{"time":605000,"text":"This one's several stories tall."},{"time":607000,"text":"In it, you'll see that it's a habitat for a lot of different animals."},{"time":611000,"text":"There's a funny kind of hot plate here, with vent water coming out of it."},{"time":614000,"text":"So all of these are individual homes for worms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"Now here's a closer view of that community."},{"time":619000,"text":"Here's crabs here, worms here."},{"time":621000,"text":"There are smaller animals crawling around."},{"time":623000,"text":"Here's pagoda structures."},{"time":625000,"text":"I think this is the neatest-looking thing."},{"time":627000,"text":"I just can't get over this --"},{"time":629000,"text":"that you've got these little chimneys sitting here smoking away."},{"time":631000,"text":"This stuff is toxic as hell, by the way."},{"time":633000,"text":"You could never get a permit to dump this in the ocean,"},{"time":635000,"text":"and it's coming out all from it."},{"time":637000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":642000,"text":"It's unbelievable. It's basically sulfuric acid,"},{"time":644000,"text":"and it's being just dumped out, at incredible rates."},{"time":647000,"text":"And animals are thriving -- and we probably came from here."},{"time":649000,"text":"That's probably where we evolved from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"BL: This bacteria that we've been talking about"},{"time":653000,"text":"turns out to be the most simplest form of life found."},{"time":658000,"text":"There are a number of groups that are proposing"},{"time":660000,"text":"that life evolved at these vent sites."},{"time":662000,"text":"Although the vent sites are short-lived --"},{"time":664000,"text":"an individual site may last only 10 years or so --"},{"time":668000,"text":"as an ecosystem they've been stable for millions -- well, billions -- of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"DG: It works too well. You see there're some fish inside here as well."},{"time":676000,"text":"There's a fish sitting here."},{"time":678000,"text":"Here's a crab with his claw right at the end of that tube worm,"},{"time":681000,"text":"waiting for that worm to stick his head out."},{"time":683000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"BL: The biologists right now cannot explain"},{"time":687000,"text":"why these animals are so active."},{"time":689000,"text":"The worms are growing inches per week!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"DG: I already said that this site,"},{"time":693000,"text":"from a human perspective, is toxic as hell."},{"time":695000,"text":"Not only that, but on top -- the lifeblood --"},{"time":698000,"text":"that plumbing system turns off every year or so."},{"time":701000,"text":"Their plumbing system turns off, so the sites have to move."},{"time":703000,"text":"And then there's earthquakes,"},{"time":705000,"text":"and then volcanic eruptions, on the order of one every five years,"},{"time":708000,"text":"that completely wipes the area out."},{"time":710000,"text":"Despite that, these animals grow back in about a year's time."},{"time":713000,"text":"You're talking about biodensities and biodiversity, again,"},{"time":717000,"text":"higher than the rainforest that just springs back to life."},{"time":720000,"text":"Is it sensitive? Yes."},{"time":722000,"text":"Is it fragile? No, it's not really very fragile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"I'll end up with saying one thing."},{"time":726000,"text":"There's a story in the sea, in the waters of the sea,"},{"time":728000,"text":"in the sediments and the rocks of the sea floor."},{"time":730000,"text":"It's an incredible story."},{"time":732000,"text":"What we see when we look back in time,"},{"time":734000,"text":"in those sediments and rocks, is a record of Earth history."},{"time":737000,"text":"Everything on this planet -- everything -- works by cycles and rhythms."},{"time":741000,"text":"The continents move apart. They come back together."},{"time":743000,"text":"Oceans come and go. Mountains come and go. Glaciers come and go."},{"time":746000,"text":"El Nino comes and goes. It's not a disaster, it's rhythmic."},{"time":748000,"text":"What we're learning now, it's almost like a symphony."},{"time":751000,"text":"It's just like music -- it really is just like music."},{"time":753000,"text":"And what we're learning now is that"},{"time":755000,"text":"you can't listen to a five-billion-year long symphony, get to today and say,"},{"time":759000,"text":"\"Stop! We want tomorrow's note to be the same as it was today.\""},{"time":762000,"text":"It's absurd. It's just absurd."},{"time":764000,"text":"So, what we've got to learn now is to find out where this planet's going"},{"time":767000,"text":"at all these different scales and work with it."},{"time":769000,"text":"Learn to manage it."},{"time":771000,"text":"The concept of preservation is futile."},{"time":773000,"text":"Conservation's tougher, but we can probably get there."},{"time":775000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":777000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":779000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}